snippet.textDisplay:
I see what you did hear Shane. 👏👏👏🧐😒😑😏🙄🤔🤭🤣 You had a "STRANGE" ER at your house not too long ago that legit scared you guys. So in order to get more eyes on this channel, you made the title "Confronting my STRANGE new addiction". Because it looked like " Confronting my stranger", and yes I'm sure it didn't fool all of you... But for simpletons like myself that agree to Apple, Google, and Facebooks Terms of Service without batting an eye, stuff like that works.
I watched 15 minutes of this video before coming to the realization that I had been HAD. Very very clever kitty. I can't even hate on you for it. So I won't. Props to successfully engaging my attention for a full 15 minutes while I ate a bowl of Kroger brand Frosted Flakes that were on sale were $1.47.

Side note: I poured a second bowl of cereal after i stopped watching your video. So I sat down, (again) new bowl of Kroger brand Frosted Flakes in hand and "thought you know, I'm going to comment on this here video (even though your likely to never see it this anyways) and let em know!

And wouldn't you know it, I finish my pointless ass comment, only to take a bite out of what seemed to be soggy pieces of cardboard. My off-brand cereal had gotten soggy. Anyways, this has just been the past 30 or so minutes of my life, but this has constantly been my life for the past 27 years. I've been through much worse, so I'll happily eat my soggy cereal and watch the remainder of your video just for the hell of it. Because why not?







I've been a fan of yours since 2007,keep up the great work. Glad to see all your years of hard work, struggles, and everything between finally pay off for you. I guess dreams can come true, your the living proof. 🤟😎👍
